article.headline: Idaho State 74, Idaho 70
article.story: POCATELLO, Idaho (AP) -- Doug D'Amore scored 21 points and came up with the crucial play down the stretch as Idaho State defeated Idaho 74-70 Wednesday night. With the game tied at 68, D'Amore stole the ball with 1:17 left, drove down the court, hit a layup and was fouled. He converted the free throw to give the Bengals (3-3) a 71-68 lead they never lost. Idaho (0-7) used a 10-3 scoring run to tie the game at 68 with three minutes left. That's when D'Amore made the play of the night. The Bengals trailed 40-36 at the break but regained control midway through the second half. Slim Millien had 14 second half points including three dunks to lead the way for Idaho State. He finished the night with 21 points. Idaho was led by Dandrick Jones who had 32 points.
